.TH CMUX-SEALED 1 "2026-07-21" "HEARTH" "HEARTH cmux integration"
.SH NAME
cmux-sealed \- launch or verify a cmux workspace in the sealed (no\-egress) tier
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cmux-sealed
.RB [ --check ]
.RB [ --strict ]
.RI [ REPO ]
.br
.B cmux-sealed --install-firewall
.br
.B cmux-sealed --remove-firewall
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cmux-sealed
is the cmux\-side analog of
.BR hearth_private.sh (1).
It enforces the HEARTH \(mu cmux sealed\-tier invariant (see
.B docs/cmux/AUDIT.md
\(sc4 and ADR\-C006) and
.B fails closed:
if it cannot prove that a workspace has no path to leave the machine, it does not launch.
.PP
The structural guarantee is an OS\-level, loopback\-only egress firewall (pf), because cmux's in\-app
browser and iroh peer\-to\-peer transport have no in\-code off switch. Two further mandatory gates are
that the target
.I REPO
classifies to the sealed tier (ADR\-C003,
.BR config/cmux/tiers.yaml )
and that HEARTH itself resolves no remote. Telemetry, auto\-update, and signed\-out state are checked
as defense\-in\-depth.
.PP
If
.I REPO
is omitted it defaults to the current directory. The default is
.B sealed:
an unclassified or unresolvable repo is treated as sealed, never open.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --check
Verify posture only; do not launch. Exit 0 iff the mandatory gates pass (and, under
.BR --strict ,
the advisory checks too).
.TP
.B --strict
Also fail on the advisory checks (telemetry off, Sparkle off, CLI\-Sentry env, signed\-out), not just
warn.
.TP
.B --install-firewall
Load the pf anchor
.B cmux-sealed
from
.B scripts/cmux/cmux-sealed.pf.conf
(requires sudo). This is the structural egress seal.
.TP
.B --remove-firewall
Flush the pf anchor (requires sudo).
.SH "MANDATORY GATES"
.IP \(bu 3
.B tier:
REPO classifies as sealed via
.BR config/cmux/tiers.yaml .
.IP \(bu 3
.B hearth:
.B scripts/hearth_private.sh --check
passes (0 remotes, all classes local/never).
.IP \(bu 3
.B firewall:
the pf anchor
.B cmux-sealed
is loaded with a block rule (loopback\-only egress).
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Sealed posture verified.
.TP
.B 2
Not sealed \(em a mandatory gate (or, under
.BR --strict ,
an advisory check) failed; launch refused.
.TP
.B 64
Usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B config/cmux/tiers.yaml
Tier classification policy (example:
.BR config/cmux/tiers.example.yaml ).
.TP
.B scripts/cmux/cmux-sealed.pf.conf
pf rules for the loopback\-only egress seal.
.TP
.B scripts/cmux/cmux_egress_probe.sh
Dynamic lsof/nettop probe to confirm a running cmux is loopback\-only.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR hearth_private.sh (1),
.BR pfctl (8),
.B docs/cmux/AUDIT.md ,
.B docs/cmux/PRIVACY.md ,
.B docs/cmux/DECISIONS.md
.SH NOTES
Path rules in
.B tiers.yaml
are matched against the
.B canonicalized
repo path (symlinks resolved): on macOS
.B /tmp
resolves to
.BR /private/tmp .
Write rules against the real (resolved) location.
.SH CAVEAT
This seals the cmux cockpit. It does not seal a frontier agent you run inside a pane over confidential
files \(em choose the pane's agent by the data's sensitivity (see
.B docs/cmux/PRIVACY.md
\(dq the caller caveat\(dq).
